      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my nest thermostat is acting weird. i keep waking up in the middle of the night because the temp dropped like 10 degrees and i dont have any schedules set for that time. what could be causing this?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sudden drop in temperature can be quite unsettling, especially when you're trying to get a good night's sleep. It's possible that your nest thermostat is experiencing a temporary glitch or a minor software issue, which is causing it to malfunction. You might want to check the Nest app for any updates or notifications, and also ensure that your thermostat is properly connected to the internet and that the Wi-Fi signal is strong. It's also worth checking the thermostat's settings to see if there are any unusual or automated adjustments that might be causing the temperature to drop unexpectedly. \n\nYou can also try resetting the thermostat by pressing the small button on the side for about 5 seconds. This will likely resolve the issue, but if the problem persists, you may need to contact Nest support for further assistance. \n\nIt's worth noting that a sudden drop in temperature can also be caused by external factors such as a power outage, a nearby construction site, or a neighbor's heating system. However, in most cases, it's a software or connectivity issue with your Nest thermostat.",
